               <p>SARAH HARMAN. I am <rs id="t18281204-231-viclabel1219" type="occupation">single</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-231-victim1991 t18281204-231-viclabel1219"></join>. On the 20th of November I asked the prisoner to go and shew me the way to a pawnbroker's, at Pimlico, where my gown was in pawn; we got it out, and he took it under his arm; I asked him for it - he said he would carry it; when we came to <placeName id="t18281204-231-crimeloc1220">Tothill-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-231-crimeloc1220" type="placeName" value="Tothill-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-231-crimeloc1220" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-231-off1217 t18281204-231-crimeloc1220"></join> we went to Mr. Jones', to get a ring out of pawn - I asked the prisoner to read the duplicate, which he did, and gave it to the pawnbroker; I laid my handkerchief, with the gown in it, on the counter and pulled out half a crown and two shillings - the prisoner took them up, and said he should be back in a minute or two, and went out.</p>
               <p>
            
